  "texts": [
    "This is a critical result for our analysis.",
    "It establishes not only the presence of filter bubbles, but it also indicates that with sufficiently low reliability (r < r 2), social media content has no impact on moderate voters, including those between the left (respectively the right) median and the overall median at 1/2.",
    "The intuition is given by Proposition 4.2.",
    "When r < r 2, the profit-maximizing filter bubble on the left does not include the 25th quantile of the belief distribution, and thus only the beliefs of voters that are more extreme than this could be impacted by social media content.",
    "Put simply, lowreliability content on social media affects only extremist voters, and not moderate ones."
  ],
